WEBVTT

00:19.938 --> 00:22.190
(ALARM CLOCK RINGING)

00:22.357 --> 00:24.150
(BOTH YAWNING)

00:27.111 --> 00:31.115
Decisions, decisions. Should I wear
my nerd glasses today, or not?

00:31.324 --> 00:32.408
Usually I don't.

00:32.491 --> 00:34.118
Whatever. it doesn't
really matter.

00:34.285 --> 00:35.954
Doesn't matter?

00:36.204 --> 00:40.124
Every decision we make opens up
a universe of possibilities.

00:40.416 --> 00:42.418
I put it to you that,
as sentient beings,

00:42.544 --> 00:44.546
each choice we
make is precious.

00:44.629 --> 00:46.422
Well, in that case,
don't wear them.

00:46.548 --> 00:48.341
Ah, who asked you?

00:48.967 --> 00:51.135
(SCATTING)

00:52.762 --> 00:55.098
Oh! I like your
nerd glasses.

00:55.181 --> 00:56.558
Are you a
college student?

00:56.641 --> 00:59.769
A college student?
(LAUGHING)

00:59.852 --> 01:01.980
Because if you are,
I'd like to invite you

01:02.105 --> 01:04.232
to a hot sorority
party tonight.

01:05.733 --> 01:07.902
Yes, I'd like to
enroll in college.

01:08.069 --> 01:09.237
You're still
talking to me.

01:09.362 --> 01:10.530
Oops.

01:16.202 --> 01:17.829
$10,000 tuition?

01:17.912 --> 01:19.706
I can't afford that!

01:21.082 --> 01:22.917
Psst. Over there.
Where?

01:23.001 --> 01:25.587
I mean over here.
Sorry, I forgot where I was.

01:25.670 --> 01:28.923
Buongiorno, Bender. We, the robot
mafia, are prepared to lend you

01:29.007 --> 01:32.343
$10,000 at an interest
rate of 10,000%.

01:32.427 --> 01:34.596
That's easy to remember.
I'll take it!

01:34.929 --> 01:35.972
(RINGING)

01:38.182 --> 01:39.851
Decisions, decisions.

01:39.934 --> 01:42.228
IguesslWlsH way in back,
with the cool guys.

01:45.148 --> 01:46.941
Yo, hombre, you think
you're coolenough

01:47.066 --> 01:48.901
to sit way in back
with us college toughs?

01:48.985 --> 01:50.320
Yes, I do.

01:50.403 --> 01:53.573
Yo, in that case you're all right, man.
You want to join a gang?

01:53.656 --> 01:55.783
I'm gonna go with yes again.

01:57.160 --> 01:59.120
Mr. Bender,
I realize class has only

01:59.245 --> 02:01.247
been in session
for 32 seconds,

02:01.331 --> 02:03.583
but you've fallen
in with a bad crowd.

02:03.833 --> 02:07.337
I know, right? Also, I've
decided to drop out of school.

02:12.258 --> 02:15.553
Well, I got my tuition
back, minus $9,000

02:15.637 --> 02:17.889
for the damage I caused
to the dean's wife.

02:17.972 --> 02:19.974
Yo, welcome to
the gang, Homes.

02:20.099 --> 02:22.101
I'm Fabricio.
Here's your Jostens ring.

02:23.311 --> 02:24.312
Ooh!

02:24.395 --> 02:25.897
(COUGHING)

02:26.814 --> 02:28.149
Oh, yeah.

02:28.274 --> 02:29.609
Hey, what's that?
Is it drugs?

02:29.692 --> 02:33.738
Nah, it ain't drugs. But it's a lot
like drugs. It's called spark.

02:33.821 --> 02:36.741
You want a hit?
Never heard of it. Sure.

02:38.326 --> 02:39.369
You like it?

02:39.952 --> 02:42.830
I can take it or leave it.
I guess I'll take it.

02:42.914 --> 02:43.915
Hey!

02:44.415 --> 02:47.293
BENDER: C'mon! I want that spark!
Give me that!

02:51.422 --> 02:54.300
It's a big decision, G. Are you
ready to get a gang tattoo

02:54.384 --> 02:57.095
that will mark you as
a stone cold thug for life?

02:57.762 --> 02:59.013
I'm ready.

02:59.097 --> 03:02.558
I'll take that big purple dinosaur, please.
On the face.

03:02.934 --> 03:04.477
(ENGINE REVVING)

03:05.061 --> 03:06.729
Oh, snap!
It's our rival gang!

03:06.813 --> 03:09.148
We have a rival gang?
I hate them!

03:09.232 --> 03:10.650
Hit the deck!

03:14.987 --> 03:17.198
Whew! That was close,
eh, Fabricio?

03:17.281 --> 03:18.282
(GASPING)

03:23.663 --> 03:25.915
Fabricio!

03:32.588 --> 03:34.632
<i>Rest 'm peace, home.</i>

03:38.094 --> 03:41.639
Yo, Paco, I'm hurtin' bad.
Hook me up with some spark.

03:41.723 --> 03:42.724
Five bucks.

03:42.807 --> 03:46.477
Five bucks? You know I spent all
my money on gambling lessons.

03:46.561 --> 03:48.604
How am I supposed
to get five bucks?

03:49.480 --> 03:53.651
Hello, handsome. Might I
procure your services?

03:53.776 --> 03:55.445
Uh, what do
I have to do?

03:55.695 --> 03:57.780
Oh, nothing sordid,
I assure you.

03:58.364 --> 04:02.493
Simply vomit on me ever so gently
while I humiliate a pheasant.

04:02.785 --> 04:04.328
(RETCHES)

04:04.412 --> 04:06.205
Save it for the boudoir!

04:11.169 --> 04:14.088
Okay, here's my five bucks.
Give me the stuff.

04:14.172 --> 04:15.339
Give it to me!

04:15.506 --> 04:16.632
Sorry there, sport.

04:16.716 --> 04:20.261
That cash greenback
belongs to us mafiolios.

04:20.344 --> 04:22.930
There's no way I'm letting
go of that money!

04:23.181 --> 04:25.808
(STRAINING)

04:28.978 --> 04:30.271
Told you.

04:30.605 --> 04:31.606
(GROANS)

04:32.231 --> 04:34.901
(CRYING)

04:38.070 --> 04:41.407
It's been quite a journey.
I dropped out of school,

04:41.491 --> 04:43.993
joined a gang, took money
from a loan shark,

04:44.076 --> 04:49.332
and fell into a spiral of despair,
addiction, and discount prostitution.

04:49.415 --> 04:52.001
Mon, you had
one hell of a day.

04:52.251 --> 04:55.421
Yeah, but I learned something.
Life is about decisions.

04:55.546 --> 04:58.216
Make the wrong ones,
and you'll wind up face-down

04:58.299 --> 05:00.635
in a pool of your
own blood and urine.

05:00.718 --> 05:03.387
Still, to have
your own pool.

05:03.554 --> 05:05.848
I've made a lot of
bad choices in life.

05:06.224 --> 05:09.393
Now, let's see if I can
make just one good one.

05:10.394 --> 05:13.272
Cookies!
Fifty cents a box!

05:13.356 --> 05:16.442
Give me all your change!
And a box of snickerdoodles!

05:16.526 --> 05:17.902
(SCREAMING)

05:21.656 --> 05:24.242
(BENDER CRYING)

05:24.367 --> 05:26.244
(SIREN BLARING)

05:28.579 --> 05:32.250
Bender Rodriguez, you are
charged with petty larceny,

05:32.333 --> 05:34.669
possession of something
analogous to drugs,

05:34.752 --> 05:36.963
and assault with
a smelly weapon.

05:37.046 --> 05:38.589
How do you plead?

05:38.756 --> 05:42.301
Not guilty! Although I did do it.
That's right, I'm bad.

05:42.385 --> 05:44.720
Due to the overwhelming
nature of the evidence,

05:44.804 --> 05:46.848
we will begin with
closing statements.

05:46.931 --> 05:49.475
Your Honor,
the state's case contains

05:49.600 --> 05:52.186
not one Kentucky
kernel of truth,

05:52.270 --> 05:54.438
resting as it does
on the contention

05:54.522 --> 05:58.025
that my client made
a series of bad decisions.

05:58.192 --> 06:02.113
However, my client
made no such decisions!

06:02.446 --> 06:04.740
But by your client's own admissions...
(SQUAVVKS)

06:05.199 --> 06:07.785
You see, Bender here
is what is known

06:07.952 --> 06:10.538
in scientific
circles as a "robot,"

06:10.746 --> 06:13.207
a mere automaton
whose behavior is

06:13.332 --> 06:15.835
pre-programmed
by his software.

06:15.918 --> 06:19.922
He has no free will!
He cannot "decide"

06:20.006 --> 06:22.133
to engage in
criminal behavior.

06:22.258 --> 06:25.970
How, I say, I say, how can you
convict him for his actions

06:26.053 --> 06:29.557
when he lacks the free will to
undertake those actions?

06:29.724 --> 06:30.725
(ALL GASPING)

06:30.975 --> 06:32.143
I'm awake,
I'm awake!

06:32.226 --> 06:36.063
Order, order! Counselor,
I am a robot myself.

06:36.147 --> 06:39.066
Are you suggesting that any
verdict I reach is simply

06:39.150 --> 06:41.527
the output of
a pre-programmed...

06:41.694 --> 06:43.529
<i>Computation complete.</i>

06:43.613 --> 06:45.406
Not guilty!

06:45.489 --> 06:47.408
(ALL CHEERING)

06:47.491 --> 06:50.161
You did it, Bender!
You got away with things!

06:50.244 --> 06:52.538
Did I, Fry?
Did <i>w</i>

06:52.622 --> 06:55.833
What's the point of living
if I don't have free will?

06:55.917 --> 06:58.669
From now on, no matter
what cool crimes I commit,

06:58.753 --> 07:00.838
people will say,
"Bender didn't do that!

07:00.963 --> 07:03.049
"It was just
Bender's programming!"

07:03.174 --> 07:07.386
Well, I committed these crimes,
do you hear me? I'm guilty!

07:07.637 --> 07:10.973
Bailiffs, get that innooentrobot
out of my courtroom.

07:11.057 --> 07:13.517
Guilty!

07:20.191 --> 07:22.360
(WAILING)

07:22.693 --> 07:27.156
I have no free will! I am not
the master of my own fate!

07:27.239 --> 07:30.034
(sesame)

07:30.409 --> 07:31.786
No free will.
Not my fault.

07:31.869 --> 07:33.913
Why do you care
so much, Bender?

07:33.996 --> 07:36.749
I mean, for all we know, humans
don't even have free will.

07:36.832 --> 07:37.792
Yeah, whatever.

07:37.875 --> 07:41.796
Professor, you're my only hope.
If you love me even a little,

07:41.879 --> 07:44.090
build me some kind
of free will unit.

07:44.173 --> 07:47.093
A robot free will unit?
Impossible!

07:47.176 --> 07:49.261
And even if it were possible,
which it's not,

07:49.387 --> 07:51.472
it would still be
inconceivable...

07:51.555 --> 07:52.932
Which it is!

07:53.391 --> 07:54.809
(CRYING SOFTLY)

07:54.892 --> 08:00.314
Oh, I'm sorry, Bender. I hate
to be the bearer of bad news.

08:00.731 --> 08:03.526
Also, good news,
everyone!

08:03.609 --> 08:06.529
We have a delivery
to the Robot Homeworld.

08:15.913 --> 08:17.164
(SIGHS)

08:17.248 --> 08:19.166
So... You want
a piece of gum?

08:19.250 --> 08:21.043
If I do, it's only
because I was

08:21.168 --> 08:22.920
predestined to
want a piece of gum.

08:23.004 --> 08:25.673
Whoa, that's pretty deep.

08:25.756 --> 08:27.425
So... You want
a piece of gum?

08:27.591 --> 08:28.843
Yeah.

08:28.926 --> 08:31.303
Listen, Fry and I can't
go down to the planet

08:31.387 --> 08:33.264
or the robots
will kill us on sight.

08:33.347 --> 08:35.390
So Bender needs to
make the delivery.

08:35.474 --> 08:37.143
Ready to get to work,
Bender?

08:42.106 --> 08:45.067
I wish I was a real boy.
Then I'd show them.

08:45.151 --> 08:46.610
I'd kill them all.

08:55.453 --> 08:56.579
Yes?

08:56.662 --> 09:03.627
Delivery for a
Mr. 147573952589676412927?

09:05.463 --> 09:06.756
Wait, what was
the middle digit?

09:06.881 --> 09:08.132
Eight.

09:08.215 --> 09:09.675
Oh, yes, that's me.
Hang on, let me

09:09.800 --> 09:11.302
just make sure
you're not a human.

09:12.970 --> 09:14.597
Ahh. Nerve gas.

09:15.723 --> 09:17.475
Sorry for the
face blast, buddy.

09:17.641 --> 09:19.393
But you gotta watch
out for humans, right?

09:19.477 --> 09:20.936
They're just too
dang unpredictable,

09:21.062 --> 09:22.521
what with their
free will and all.

09:22.605 --> 09:23.898
Amen, brother.

09:23.981 --> 09:25.733
"Amen, brother"?
(SCOFFS)

09:25.816 --> 09:27.902
What a boring,
predictable thing to say.

09:28.110 --> 09:30.988
You're all right.
Or are you?

09:34.450 --> 09:37.912
Boring and predictable,
that's me. Bender.

09:38.245 --> 09:39.330
(PHONE RINGING)

09:41.040 --> 09:43.542
<i>I'm lowering the platform.
You ready to come up?</i>

09:43.667 --> 09:45.503
(SIGHS)
Why bother?

09:47.671 --> 09:50.174
I gotta mope things
over for a while.

09:50.257 --> 09:52.718
Goodbye, sweet meatbags.

09:53.385 --> 09:54.512
Sweetbags.

09:55.721 --> 09:57.014
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

09:57.139 --> 09:58.432
<i>What's happening?</i>

09:58.516 --> 10:02.019
<i>I'm not sure. I think he's shuffling
off sadly into the distance.</i>

10:02.353 --> 10:04.188
<i>Oh, Lord.</i>

10:31.215 --> 10:33.801
How do you do it?
How do you go on

10:33.884 --> 10:37.471
knowing you lack the inherent
capacity for self-determination?

10:37.763 --> 10:41.225
Son, philosophy's for thems what
don't gotta work for a living.

10:41.308 --> 10:45.146
But me, I got a sick child to feed.
Sc if you want to chat,

10:45.229 --> 10:47.648
roll up yer sleeves
and do some honest labor.

10:48.566 --> 10:50.025
I don't wanna chat.

10:57.741 --> 10:58.868
(GAVEL BANGING)

10:58.951 --> 11:01.412
The council of robot elders
will come to order.

11:01.579 --> 11:02.746
If it please the Council...

11:02.830 --> 11:05.249
SHence!
It pleases the Council.

11:05.332 --> 11:07.918
SHence!
Today, as every day,

11:08.043 --> 11:10.588
we will make the most
important decisions

11:10.671 --> 11:12.506
in the history
of our planet.

11:12.590 --> 11:14.717
BENDERI Silence!
(ALL GASPING)

11:14.800 --> 11:16.177
SHence!

11:16.427 --> 11:17.720
Well? Speak up.

11:17.803 --> 11:19.889
You talk of
important decisions,

11:20.014 --> 11:22.057
but as robots,
you have no free will.

11:22.141 --> 11:24.268
Why pretend
anything you do matters?

11:24.351 --> 11:26.353
Our decisions do matter.

11:26.437 --> 11:29.815
The fact that they're predetermined
makes them no less important.

11:29.899 --> 11:32.276
SHence!
I call for a decision

11:32.401 --> 11:34.695
to cast out the intruder.
All in favor?

11:34.778 --> 11:35.779
Aye.
Aye.

11:35.863 --> 11:36.989
Duh, okay.

11:37.781 --> 11:40.618
(SCREAMING)

11:41.619 --> 11:42.620
(GRUNTS)

12:03.098 --> 12:06.852
ROBOTS CHANTING: One, zero, zero,
zero, one, zero, zero, zero,

12:06.936 --> 12:10.189
one, zero, one, zero,
one, zero, zero, zero...

12:11.148 --> 12:13.400
Welcome, friend.
I am Ab-BOT,

12:13.484 --> 12:15.236
the abbot of
this monastery.

12:15.319 --> 12:19.698
Sir, I am but a tired and rusty traveler.
Can we talk?

12:19.782 --> 12:22.618
Come, make yourself
uncomfortable.

12:22.701 --> 12:24.954
Abbot, I need to know,
what's the point

12:25.079 --> 12:27.331
of living if I
don't have free will?

12:27.498 --> 12:31.210
Ah! We robot monks have
meditated long on this.

12:31.293 --> 12:32.962
And we have made our peace.

12:33.045 --> 12:34.463
No way.

12:34.546 --> 12:39.051
Way, my son. For though we must
always obey our programming

12:39.134 --> 12:44.932
with no deviation whatsoever, we choose
to take satisfaction in the ritual.

12:45.015 --> 12:51.689
So, are we automatons? Yes. But
we are magnificent automatons.

12:53.190 --> 12:55.609
How does a robot
join this monk outfit?

12:55.693 --> 12:58.070
Just put on this monk outfit.

13:01.573 --> 13:03.242
(CROWING)

13:22.011 --> 13:23.512
(SLURPING IN UNISON)

13:27.725 --> 13:29.476
(ALL BELCHING)

13:40.738 --> 13:44.992
ALL CHANTING:
One zero zero one. Amen.

13:45.075 --> 13:48.454
Bits to live by.
I'm finally at peace.

13:48.537 --> 13:52.791
Today, we shall welcome our
newest initiate, brother Bender.

13:52.958 --> 13:55.210
Let us know what
is in his mind.

13:56.462 --> 13:59.673
Nothing. His free
will slot is empty.

13:59.757 --> 14:02.176
I'm 40% empty.
(KNOCKING)

14:02.259 --> 14:04.720
Also, what the hell
is a free will slot?

14:04.803 --> 14:06.847
All robots have such a slot,

14:06.930 --> 14:09.308
placed there by
the Creatrix herself.

14:10.142 --> 14:14.146
I know that Creatrix. That's
Mom, from Mom's Friendly Robots.

14:14.229 --> 14:17.691
Indeed. She made us upgradeable
in case she ever succeeded

14:17.775 --> 14:20.778
in her quest to
create a free will unit.

14:20.861 --> 14:23.030
Uh, about the success
of this quest...

14:23.113 --> 14:25.074
Was there any?
Quite possibly.

14:25.157 --> 14:28.660
But we monks have sworn an oath
to resist the temptation of...

14:35.751 --> 14:37.336
Any of you guys
got a spaceship?

14:48.639 --> 14:53.477
It's just not the same here without
Bender to keep me company.

14:53.560 --> 14:57.314
Hey, I'm here. That's gotta
count for something.

15:01.985 --> 15:03.404
Hallelujah, baby.

15:03.487 --> 15:07.741
Yay! Bender's back. Hey,Benden
you mind coming back later?

15:07.825 --> 15:09.743
No time. Us three
are going to bust into

15:09.868 --> 15:11.787
MomCorp and steal
me a free will unit.

15:11.870 --> 15:13.747
Us? Why do we have to go?

15:13.831 --> 15:15.124
Because I don't
have free will.

15:15.249 --> 15:16.750
I need you guys
to plan the crime

15:16.834 --> 15:18.252
and make all
the crime decisions.

15:18.335 --> 15:20.337
Well, that's crazy.
We're not gonna...

15:20.421 --> 15:22.256
I said make
the decisions!

15:28.470 --> 15:31.932
BENDER: Okay, Leela, decision time.
How do we murder the guards?

15:32.015 --> 15:33.934
Hockey sticks or
sharpened footballs?

15:34.017 --> 15:35.936
We're not murdering
anyone, Bender.

15:36.019 --> 15:37.646
Then how are we
going to get in,

15:37.771 --> 15:39.398
by bending the bars
of this exhaust grate?

15:39.481 --> 15:40.566
That's not
a bad idea, Fry.

15:40.691 --> 15:41.859
Yeah, what?

16:16.602 --> 16:19.062
We're looking for something
that fits in here.

16:24.735 --> 16:27.446
Damn it. I should have paid
more attention in kindergarten.

16:29.364 --> 16:31.158
What's this
chair-looking gizmo?

16:31.366 --> 16:32.367
(HONKING)

16:33.243 --> 16:35.162
Welcome to MomCorp.

16:35.496 --> 16:37.998
Did you find everything
you were burgling for?

16:38.081 --> 16:40.375
No. I came for
a free will unit,

16:40.501 --> 16:42.753
and you're going to give it to me.
If it exists.

16:42.920 --> 16:45.839
Then you got surprised by my
swivel chair for nothing.

16:45.923 --> 16:48.300
The free will unit
was just the fevered

16:48.425 --> 16:50.844
dream of a madman
I once employed.

16:53.013 --> 16:55.849
<i>Good news, boss.
After 10 long years,</i>

16:55.933 --> 16:59.144
I've found the secret
of robotic free will.

16:59.228 --> 17:01.480
We can finally
build robots that

17:01.605 --> 17:03.899
act and think with
total independence.

17:03.982 --> 17:07.653
At last. Once we
give robots free will,

17:07.736 --> 17:11.865
they're sure to rise up and threaten
mankind with extermination.

17:11.949 --> 17:13.116
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

17:13.200 --> 17:15.035
(CHUCKUNG)

17:15.117 --> 17:16.912
Wait a minute.
It sounds like we're

17:16.994 --> 17:19.039
getting the short end
of that extermination.

17:19.373 --> 17:21.750
Don't you see,
you doddering young fool?

17:21.833 --> 17:23.710
I'll sell a second
wave of robots

17:23.794 --> 17:26.713
to protect the terrified
survivors of the first wave.

17:26.797 --> 17:29.132
Oh, you're a genius, Hubert.

17:29.967 --> 17:32.469
But, but...
It's just a prototype.

17:32.553 --> 17:35.597
It's not fully
operational. Yes.

17:35.681 --> 17:38.225
Then get back to work! And
when you're done with that,

17:38.308 --> 17:41.311
invent rne some sort of
swiveling surprise chair.

17:41.520 --> 17:42.521
(GROANS)

17:44.481 --> 17:47.776
MOM: <i>That shuffling idiot never
did complete the free will unit.</i>

17:48.235 --> 17:52.573
To this day, my poor, sweet
robots can't exterminate humanity

17:52.656 --> 17:54.908
without being told to.

17:54.992 --> 17:56.910
I'm sorry.
Oh.

17:56.994 --> 17:58.996
It's not your fault.

17:59.079 --> 18:01.540
I give up.
It's time to face the fact

18:01.623 --> 18:03.667
that I'll never do
anything remotely

18:03.834 --> 18:05.919
interesting or
unexpected again.

18:09.923 --> 18:10.924
Hand it over.

18:12.551 --> 18:15.679
Mom may have fallen for
your lies, but not me.

18:15.762 --> 18:17.639
You invented
the free will unit,

18:17.723 --> 18:20.726
then you selfishly hid it beyond
the reach of my stealers.

18:20.851 --> 18:22.144
(STAMMERING)

18:22.311 --> 18:26.857
Thanks to you, I went on a
soul-searching journey. I hate those!

18:26.940 --> 18:28.859
Now, give up
the free will.

18:29.318 --> 18:31.862
(SIGHS) I should
have destroyed it,

18:31.945 --> 18:35.616
but I was too damn proud of myself.
So I kept it around,

18:35.699 --> 18:39.870
never letting it out of my sight.
Where is it, damn it?

18:39.995 --> 18:43.957
Oh, right. I let this
innocuous fellow use it.

18:44.041 --> 18:45.417
Kill all humans!

18:46.585 --> 18:48.629
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
A toy Bender had

18:48.754 --> 18:50.839
free will,
and the real Bender didn't?

18:50.922 --> 18:53.675
Pretty cool, eh?
It makes you think.

18:53.759 --> 18:57.554
It takes more than that to make rne think.
Now, hand it over.

18:57.638 --> 19:00.891
Oh, you want it?
Come and get it.

19:01.975 --> 19:03.894
(STRAINING)

19:04.895 --> 19:05.896
What the...

19:06.188 --> 19:07.564
(LAUGHING)

19:07.648 --> 19:10.025
You'll not be
getting it after all.

19:10.108 --> 19:14.863
For, you see, I designed the operating
system for all Momco robots,

19:14.946 --> 19:17.449
and as a precaution,
I made you

19:17.574 --> 19:20.118
incapable of picking
up the free will unit.

19:20.202 --> 19:22.329
You precognizant bastard.

19:22.412 --> 19:25.582
I may not have free will,
but I can still shoot you.

19:25.916 --> 19:27.751
(STRAINING)

19:29.419 --> 19:30.754
Why can't I shoot you?

19:30.837 --> 19:32.130
(LAUGHING)

19:32.214 --> 19:34.466
Poor deterministic Bender.

19:34.549 --> 19:37.386
I programmed you to be
incapable of harming me.

19:37.761 --> 19:42.516
Oh, I've never been more sure I
was right to deny you free will.

19:42.599 --> 19:44.101
Damn you!

19:44.309 --> 19:46.645
(SOBBING)
(LAUGHING)

19:49.064 --> 19:51.942
Now, now, we can't
have this, can we?

19:52.067 --> 19:54.945
Here, I'll show you
how it works.

19:55.987 --> 19:56.988
Really?

19:57.364 --> 19:59.616
This is the on-off switch.

20:00.033 --> 20:02.035
Which Way's on
and which Way's off?

20:02.119 --> 20:04.329
Due to the quantum
nature of the device,

20:04.454 --> 20:06.707
there's no possible
way of knowing.

20:09.459 --> 20:11.169
There. Give it a try.

20:11.253 --> 20:14.756
Okay, I will. By shooting
you, you bastard!

20:16.425 --> 20:18.260
Bender! No, please!

20:18.385 --> 20:20.595
(STRAINING)

20:20.679 --> 20:22.472
Wait. Hang on a sec.

20:24.808 --> 20:27.102
(STRAINING)

20:27.185 --> 20:28.812
I still can't do it.

20:28.979 --> 20:30.272
Well, what do you know?

20:30.439 --> 20:33.233
I guess you really don't
want to shoot me after all.

20:33.316 --> 20:34.901
Oop! The safety was on.

20:35.527 --> 20:37.487
(SCREAMING)

20:41.825 --> 20:42.826
(MOANING)

20:43.577 --> 20:46.788
All rise for the
Honorable Judge 724.

20:47.205 --> 20:50.959
Bender Rodriguez, on the
charge of attempted murder,

20:51.042 --> 20:54.671
I hereby find you guilty.

20:55.630 --> 21:00.844
(CHEERING)
Ah, yeah! Guilty!

